Fully remodeled inside and out, it features a bright, open floor plan with exquisite tile work, a chefs kitchen with a large island and soft-close cabinets, quartz countertops, S/S appliances, and a newer furnace. The upper level boasts three spacious bedrooms, including a primary suite, while the lower level includes a cozy family room and a fourth bedroom. Outside, a beautiful deck provides the ideal space for relaxation or entertaining. The fully finished garage and exceptional curb appeal complete this must-see property. Come and see it today before it's gone!

Beautifully refreshed 1960's bungalow situated in the heart of Bellingham. The exterior features raised garden beds, a generous grassy backyard, and a new private patio. Inside, the kitchen has been completely modernized with a gas range, designer tile backsplash, new cabinetry, countertops, lighting and appliances. The living room includes a cozy fireplace and large bay windows with partial views of the bay. Bathrooms have been fully renovated, and the lower level offers a versatile recreation room, laundry room, additional bedroom and bathroom, along with ample storage for all your Pacific Northwest essentials. Additional updates include fresh paint, new doors, and updated flooring throughout the home!

Introducing the CedarView townhome, a 2100+ SF home with 3 beds/3.5 baths, oversized 2 car garage, and a bonus level. The upper level features a two bedrooms with full bath, and utility room with laundry & full size W/D. The main level includes a powder room, entry, kitchen with eating space, dining and living rooms, and a covered deck. Bonus level offers a spacious private covered deck, a Primary bedroom with a full bath, and a walk-in closet with connection for 2nd W/D! Each townhome includes solid wood kitchen cabinets w/soft close hardware, a fire suppression system, and solar panel upgrade available. The 10+ acre nature preserve provides a permanently protected view and a unique and tranquil living experience.

Discover your private oasis in the Pacific Northwest! Nestled within the vibrant Sudden Valley Community, this enchanting 3-bedroom, 2-bath home offers a peaceful retreat with access to beaches, a marina, golf course, public trails, parks, and more. The main living space features impressive vaulted wood ceilings, enhancing the home's welcoming atmosphere. Ascend to the primary suite, a generous room complete with a small private deck that offers breathtaking views. Set on a flat driveway and enveloped by trees, this property backs onto a green space, ensuring a sense of semi-seclusion year-round. Relish the territorial views and take the opportunity to make this delightful space your own in the heart of Sudden Valley.

Build your modern woodland sanctuary in an incredibly private location. Completed survey and geotech available PLUS pre-paid water and sewer LID. This gorgeous lot offers green belt on one side, ideal up-sloping topography, gently sloping driveway access potential, and views of wooded and steep (ie: very difficult to build on) parcels across the street. This lot is perfect for enjoying the tranquility and privacy of the woods, easy access to all of Sudden Valley's community amenities, and the Sudden Valley entrance to the Stimpson Nature Preserve just down the street.

Rare opportunity on Alabama Hill! This beautiful turnkey home on a versatile 10, 000+ sq ft gently sloping lot presents exceptional development potential. Quick access to the railroad trail allows a short walk to Whatcom Falls, Bloedel Donovan and Barkley Village. This cozy and inviting home features a gas fireplace, deck, under home storage, and detached storage shed. The cleared lot, one of the few buildable in the area, makes this a rare find for savvy investors, developers or family planners. Current zoning allows multiple ADUs, or converting the existing home to an ADU and building your dream home - with future infill zoning providing even further potential. The 35' single family height allowance can enhance seasonal views of the bay.

An updated, single level 2 bedroom 2 bathroom 1400 sq ft. home in the desirable Village at Cordata. Come enjoy this active 55+ community with amenities including a clubhouse, indoor (heated) pool, woodworking workshop and RV parking! This location is convenient to transit, shopping and medical facilities. The large eat-in kitchen has been updated with wood cabinets and granite counters. The bathroom has been updated including a zero entry shower and heated floor. Cozy living room with a gas fireplace. A newer, low-maintenance private deck to enjoy your backyard. The home has newer windows and water heater. Enjoy a garage and tons of storage inside and out. Come see this amazing property that allows for easy, active living.
nearby_schools: Northwest Educational Service District 189, Bellingham Public Schools

text: Step into your brand-new dream home! This modern gem offers a bright, open-concept design with 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, and a spacious one-car garage complete with over 200 sq. ft. of loft storage. Soaring vaulted ceilings, radiant concrete floors, and an abundance of natural light paired with sleek LED lighting create an inviting atmosphere. The primary suite features a generous walk-in closet and a luxurious spa-style shower. The kitchen shines with quartz countertops, contemporary white cabinetry, and its own dedicated water heater for added ease. Outside, enjoy a partially fenced backyard that backs onto serene green space. This home isnt just about the stunning detailsits also part of an incredible community!

5 bedroom remodeled home in the heart of Lynden. Home features 2 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms on the main floor and 3 bedrooms with a kitchenette and family room downstairs for a possible transgenerational living possibility. Located on a corner lot near shopping and downtown, fenced back yard. This home has been recently updated and is ready to move in.

Welcome to your 4 bd, 2 3/4 bth home that is NOT IN THE FLOOD ZONE!! As you step in, you'll be greeted by a bright living room w/vaulted ceilings, central A/C and a gas fireplace. The open floor plan connects the living space to the kitchen above with a generous island and dining area, making it great for cooking and entertaining. Upstairs also has 3 bds, 2 full bths and a deck overlooking the backyard ideal for barbeques or gatherings. The Primary bedroom has a regular closet, along with a walk-in closet and private full bath. The lower level has a kitchenette, 4th bedroom and a 3/4 bath with an additional laundry space w/hook ups making it ideal for either a mother-in-law suite or just a great bonus space.
